Swans
I need a seven day weekend

I work near the Tampa airport so I have planse going over all day long. Sometimes I drive down the road and just hang out at the end of the runway and have the planes bearing down on me, gliding in with flaps and landing gear sread open or blasting up into the sky, this has nothing to do with aerodimamics or wing lift its nothing but thrust from engins mussleing that hunk of metal to the air saying fuck you gravity and the planet that made you. 

I would hope that anyone who reads this would have at some point been cloud racing. I saw a great example of it during my commute the other day. Two motorcycles went ripping past me and hot on their tail was rain. It is so amazing how the rain can have such a defined border. You can actually walk into than out of the rain at times.

Some people are like Slinkies. 
They have no practical use whatsoever, 
but they still bring a smile to your face when you push them down a flight of stairs.

"Be careful of the words you say,
Keep them soft and sweet.
You never know from day to day
Which ones you'll have to eat!"

Hey all...how have you been.

Well i'm groggy and sore from Marti Gras. My new town has itself a nice little one...about 7000 people. the downtown area was closed to traffic and much fun and merry making was being flung all about. Some of the floats were outrageous...just amazing. My favorite was the Voodoo Dolls float. I don't even know were to start on that one, but they had live music on theirs and man...wow. 

Marti Gras was the second big old party this month. Earlier in the month was Gasparilla...named after the Gasparilla Sound. By what i'm told the reason for it was back in the day the pirates would roll into the area about the same time every year and loot, pillage, plunder and well be pirates. So the folks around here would have a huge ta-do before they showed up and eat and drink, consume all that they could so they could enjoy the fruits of their labor before the pirates came and took it all or worse killed them. It was much like Marti Gras but very pirate themed. 

We also had the state fair, the Strawberry Festival is coming up and K and I are gonna hit the big Ren Fair next weekend, it's chocolate and romance this week end...each weekend has a different theme. I don't know when these folks find the time to go to work in Fed and March. 

I am thinking of starting scuba lessons this month and get certified to start what I want to be my new hobbie. There is no place for 4X4s or dirt bikes here almost all fun is Gulf based here so my two thoughts were a jet ski or scuba...I'm thinking scuba but i need to start research on it as to be realistic about the cost of equipment and the maintenance of that equipment. If i cheaped out on my dirt bike worst thing would be I would have to walk, scuba well I'd hate to drowned.

In closing life is good here I hope the same for all of you.

The air is so nice this morning. Fall feels so good and has nice air.

Well so far my 1st day as a freelance human has been good. We all slept in late. Thank you Pod, but she did remove all her jamies and diaper. I took a nice drive this morning to. Coming back from Los Osos the closer hills were still in shadow while the taller ones for the Cuesta Ridge were on fire with the rising sun with very textures high clouds. Which was a very dramatic contrast to the hills on the right of the road with fingers of ocean mist reaching over. I even got rained on for about four minuets with the roof open. I am going to miss California.

It is by caffeine alone I set my mind in motion, 
It is by the beans of Java that thoughts acquire speed, 
The hands acquire shaking, the shaking becomes a warning, 
It is by caffeine alone I set my mind in motion.
